Introduction

Kursor (formerly known as Jung Ho) is a South Korean singer, songwriter, and producer. He first entered the music industry as one half of the R&B duo 2MUCH, later renamed 8LOOP, alongside TE.O. The duo debuted on April 24, 2017 under Real Slow Company, a label he is still affiliated with. Although the group became inactive as of November 17, 2017, Kursor remained active in music.

He made his solo debut on January 15, 2019 with the single "KNOT", under the independent label BIXIZ XOUND. In addition to performing, Kursor is involved in the full production of his music, including songwriting and composition. His style blends elements of R&B and other genres, and he has received recognition both in South Korea and internationally for his work.
